<i>To insure</i> <i>complete effectiveness,</i> <i>spread your feet apart.</i>

487
00:49:25,300 --> 00:49:27,690
<i>To protect scalp</i> <i>and facial hair,</i>

488
00:49:27,770 --> 00:49:30,580
<i>place the metal helmet</i> <i>securely on the head.</i>

489
00:49:35,320 --> 00:49:39,510
<i>Make sure the helmet</i> <i>is firmly seated</i> <i>and the visor lowered.</i>

490
00:49:39,580 --> 00:49:42,360
<i>Then raise your arms</i> <i>and wait.</i>

491
00:50:01,370 --> 00:50:03,820
<i>You may now remove helmet.</i>

492
00:50:05,660 --> 00:50:08,790
<i>You will notice a fine white ash</i> <i>on your body.</i>

493
00:50:08,860 --> 00:50:13,430
<i>This is the outer</i> <i>epithelial layers of your skin</i> <i>that have been burned away.</i>

494
00:50:15,290 --> 00:50:19,890
<i>Please replace the helmet</i> <i>in compartment and proceed</i> <i>through shower in next room.</i>

495
00:50:19,960 --> 00:50:22,810
<i>Then you may dress</i> <i>and descend to level 4.</i>

496
00:50:29,660 --> 00:50:33,140
We're required to rest for six hours on level 4 after exposure to the xenon lamp.

497
00:50:33,210 --> 00:50:35,250
So go to your rooms and sleep.

498
00:50:35,320 --> 00:50:37,810
At the end of the corridor is the cafeteria.

499
00:50:37,880 --> 00:50:41,330
We'll meet there at 0400 hours... tomorrow.

500
00:50:45,270 --> 00:50:47,820
<i>Pharmacology</i> <i>to maintenance L.B.</i>

501
00:50:47,900 --> 00:50:52,170
<i>One of our R.F.s shows</i> <i>six points over nominal</i> <i>at pressure 3.</i>

502
00:50:56,090 --> 00:50:59,980
<i>Watchdog to all levels.</i> <i>Scoop 7 capsule secure.</i>

503
00:51:00,060 --> 00:51:03,950
<i>Biocheck 66</i> <i>plus 9 minus OL-5.</i>

504
00:51:17,400 --> 00:51:19,500
<i>LEO control to KEEPSAKE 5.</i>

505
00:51:19,580 --> 00:51:24,690
<i>The pressure integrity check</i> <i>runs 2.54 G-CM to the second.</i>

506
00:51:24,760 --> 00:51:27,630
<i>Please confirm.</i>

507
00:51:58,650 --> 00:52:01,680
A new form of life.

508
00:52:03,610 --> 00:52:06,290
Like Rudolph Karp's bacteria.

509
00:52:06,360 --> 00:52:08,120
Fools!

510
00:52:08,180 --> 00:52:11,730
They refuse to believe life exists in meteorites.

511
00:52:11,800 --> 00:52:15,480
I showed them at the Astrophysics Conference what I just showed you.

512
00:52:15,540 --> 00:52:19,060
But no, even with a microscope, they are blind.

513
00:52:19,130 --> 00:52:21,360
What do I have to do? Hit them over the head?

514
00:52:39,800 --> 00:52:43,860
I'm glad you're amused, gentlemen, but it might just turn out to be true.

515
00:52:43,930 --> 00:52:46,420
During this symposium, we'll discuss the possibility...

516
00:52:46,490 --> 00:52:48,820
that intelligent life on a distant planet...

517
00:52:48,890 --> 00:52:52,370
may be no larger than a flea.

518
00:52:52,440 --> 00:52:55,980
Perhaps no larger than a bacterium.

519
00:52:58,620 --> 00:53:02,390
<i>Time to wake up, sir.</i>

520
00:53:02,460 --> 00:53:05,360
<i>Time to wake up, sir!</i>

521
00:53:09,660 --> 00:53:11,510
Hello?

522
00:53:11,580 --> 00:53:14,190
<i>Time to wake up, sir.</i>

523
00:53:15,580 --> 00:53:19,700
Who are you? <i>Time to wake up, sir.</i>

524
00:53:25,500 --> 00:53:27,730
Do you wish something, sir?

525
00:53:27,800 --> 00:53:29,690
Your name.

526
00:53:29,750 --> 00:53:32,530
Will that be all, sir?

527
00:53:32,600 --> 00:53:34,450
For the moment.

528
00:53:55,670 --> 00:53:58,220
<i>This is the</i> <i>answering service supervisor.</i>

529
00:53:58,300 --> 00:54:01,780
<i>We wish you would adopt</i> <i>a more serious attitude, Dr. Hall.</i>

530
00:54:01,850 --> 00:54:04,340
Sorry. Her voice is quite luscious.

531
00:54:04,410 --> 00:54:08,560
<i>The voice belongs</i> <i>to Miss Gladys Stevens</i> <i>who is 63 years old.</i>

532
00:54:08,630 --> 00:54:13,270
<i>She lives in Omaha and</i> <i>makes her living taping messages</i> <i>for voice-reminder systems.</i>

533
00:54:13,340 --> 00:54:15,670
Much obliged.

534
00:54:15,740 --> 00:54:19,380
<i>Let's not get sidetracked</i> <i>on Rudolph Karp</i> <i>and his meteorite theories.</i>

535
00:54:19,450 --> 00:54:21,360
His technique was worthless!

536
00:54:21,430 --> 00:54:24,750
I still think we should contact him. Fair enough. Where is he?

537
00:54:24,820 --> 00:54:28,240
Behind the Iron Curtain. He couldn't get a research grant here.

538
00:54:31,800 --> 00:54:35,600
<i>H.P. nutrient now available</i> <i>in the cafeteria...</i>

539
00:54:35,670 --> 00:54:38,770
<i>for staff members</i> <i>from sectors 1 through 6.</i>

540
00:54:38,840 --> 00:54:41,940
Hemlock! All for you, Hippocrates.

541
00:54:42,010 --> 00:54:43,950
Not your own venom?

542
00:54:45,940 --> 00:54:48,280
Tastes like orange juice.

543
00:54:48,340 --> 00:54:50,350
Nutrient 42-5.

544
00:54:50,420 --> 00:54:52,150
Developed for the astronauts.

545
00:54:52,220 --> 00:54:54,870
Eight ounces satisfy all daily nutritional requirements.

546
00:54:54,940 --> 00:54:56,720
Except coffee.

547
00:54:56,790 --> 00:54:59,090
And lipid soluble vitamins.

548
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:01,580
For that we have these. Help yourself.

549
00:55:01,660 --> 00:55:03,860
So what's the point of the cafeteria?

550
00:55:03,930 --> 00:55:08,050
Wildfire isn't always on crash status. Maybe there's some sugar.

551
00:55:08,120 --> 00:55:11,020
Nope. Nothing that might provide a bacterial growth medium.

552
00:55:11,100 --> 00:55:12,980
Precisely. No sugar in the gut.

553
00:55:13,050 --> 00:55:15,220
I'd like a cigarette right now.

554
00:55:15,290 --> 00:55:18,520
It's after meals you miss 'em. <i>You should have</i> <i>no trouble on level 5.</i>

555
00:55:18,580 --> 00:55:20,790
You won't even get this close to a meal.

556
00:55:20,860 --> 00:55:23,220
We'll be entirely on high-protein nutrients.

557
00:55:23,290 --> 00:55:25,560
I planned our work in three stages.

558
00:55:25,620 --> 00:55:27,510
One: detection.

559
00:55:27,580 --> 00:55:30,160
First step is to confirm that an organism is present.

560
00:55:30,230 --> 00:55:33,680
Two: characterization. How's it structured, how does it work?

561
00:55:33,750 --> 00:55:36,400
Three: control.

562
00:55:36,470 --> 00:55:38,860
How to contain and exterminate?

563
00:55:38,940 --> 00:55:42,280
Jeremy, on this matter of extermination, we should go slowly.

564
00:55:42,360 --> 00:55:46,390
Without ever realizing it, we might destroy a highly intelligent form of life.

565
00:55:46,460 --> 00:55:49,270
Why don't we get going? I've got two patients down there.

566
00:55:49,340 --> 00:55:52,400
- The team has two subjects. - They're not guinea pigs, Stone.

567
00:55:53,750 --> 00:55:57,070
<i>You may now proceed to level 5,</i> <i>gentlemen.</i>

568
00:56:02,740 --> 00:56:07,630
Um, stop by your rooms and insert these before taking the elevator.

569
00:56:07,700 --> 00:56:10,320
I have risked drowning in that foul bath.

570
00:56:10,390 --> 00:56:13,970
I have been parboiled, irradiated and xenon flashed. And now you suggest I...

571
00:56:14,040 --> 00:56:16,760
I have to! We haven't done anything about the G.I. tract yet.

572
00:56:16,820 --> 00:56:19,920
On level 5 we must be as nearly germ free as possible.

573
00:56:21,820 --> 00:56:24,980
Anyone care to join me for a smoke?

574
00:56:27,100 --> 00:56:29,140
<i>Watchdog to level 2, sector D.</i>

575
00:56:29,210 --> 00:56:31,540
<i>You are</i> <i>Red Kappa Phoenix status.</i>

576
00:56:32,760 --> 00:56:35,150
<i>Off the main corridor</i> <i>on the outer rim...</i>

577
00:56:35,220 --> 00:56:40,310
<i>are the living quarters,</i> <i>conference room, cafeteria,</i> <i>bio-safety maintenance, etc.</i>

578
00:56:40,380 --> 00:56:42,320
<i>Inside are the labs.</i>

579
00:56:42,390 --> 00:56:44,600
Where is the library?

580
00:56:44,660 --> 00:56:47,860
No need for books. Everything's in the computer.

581
00:56:47,930 --> 00:56:50,320
Notice the capsule has already been delivered...

582
00:56:50,390 --> 00:56:55,890
<i>by the sterile</i> <i>conveyor system to</i> <i>the main control lab here.</i>

583
00:56:55,960 --> 00:56:59,120
<i>Your patients are here</i> <i>in the hot room</i> <i>of miscellaneous.</i>

584
00:56:59,190 --> 00:57:01,880
We can't have any direct contact with them. Poor souls.

585
00:57:01,940 --> 00:57:06,320
<i>Dr. Dutton</i> <i>and Dr. Hall are wanted</i> <i>in main control immediately.</i>

586
00:57:08,090 --> 00:57:10,510
<i>Hey!</i>

587
00:57:10,580 --> 00:57:13,550
If the patients are sealed off, how do I get to them?

588
00:57:13,620 --> 00:57:15,530
Ever used a glove box? No.

589
00:57:15,610 --> 00:57:17,680
Wildfire's gone a step further.

590
00:57:17,750 --> 00:57:20,120
Whole rooms that operate like glove boxes.

591
00:57:20,180 --> 00:57:22,040
You'll be working in one shortly.

592
00:57:33,020 --> 00:57:37,520
<i>We have a magnetic "K" indices.</i> <i>Give us a code 3</i> <i>when you get it.</i>

593
00:57:53,300 --> 00:57:55,690
I wanted you here while we find out...

594
00:57:55,770 --> 00:57:58,480
if there's anything still biologically active in the capsule.

595
00:57:58,550 --> 00:58:00,920
Suggestions? Use a buffalo.

596
00:58:00,980 --> 00:58:03,090
Audio.

597
00:58:22,140 --> 00:58:24,980
<i>Detectors "E" through "G"</i> <i>correction.</i>

