00:59:03,290 --> 00:59:06,700
Whatever killed them at Piedmont is still there and still as potent as ever.

603
00:59:06,780 --> 00:59:09,780
If potent's the word. Let's try a rhesus.

604
00:59:09,850 --> 00:59:12,300
Yeah. We'll want a postmortem on it anyway.

605
00:59:23,420 --> 00:59:25,550
<i>Housekeeping to level 5.</i>

606
00:59:25,620 --> 00:59:28,140
<i>Clean sweep schedule "B"</i> <i>now in effect.</i>

607
00:59:28,220 --> 00:59:32,080
<i>Germfree animal technicians,</i> <i>please consult schedule "A."</i>

608
01:00:22,200 --> 01:00:26,230
So, okay. Isolate and identify.

609
01:00:26,300 --> 01:00:29,200
Right. You and I'll scan the capsule, Ruth.

610
01:00:29,270 --> 01:00:33,100
Charlie, you work on these in autopsy. Open the S.L., Ruth.

611
01:01:00,120 --> 01:01:04,310
<i>Adjust S.Y. system for</i> <i>aseptricity as follows.</i>

612
01:01:04,380 --> 01:01:08,780
<i>Points 2-A at 5.</i> <i>Points 9 through 12 at plus 1.</i>

613
01:01:08,860 --> 01:01:11,920
<i>Plus 3, plus 6 at minus.</i>

614
01:01:47,770 --> 01:01:50,250
Run an initial vector study, Charlie.

615
01:01:50,330 --> 01:01:52,600
Find out how the disease enters the body.

616
01:01:53,910 --> 01:01:57,460
<i>Charlie?</i> Yes.

617
01:01:57,530 --> 01:02:02,380
Yes, the vector study first, then autopsy. Incredible.

618
01:02:04,860 --> 01:02:07,380
Dutton, be careful.

619
01:02:07,450 --> 01:02:09,520
Let our distinguished surgeon handle the knife.

620
01:02:09,590 --> 01:02:12,530
Fine, but not for a while.

621
01:02:12,600 --> 01:02:16,110
First, I'm a pediatrician and a geriatrist.

622
01:02:16,180 --> 01:02:19,790
Take it easy. Charlie will have a technician.

623
01:02:32,340 --> 01:02:34,580
What's been done for them?

624
01:02:36,600 --> 01:02:39,410
Just plasma for the old man, dextrose for the baby.

625
01:02:39,490 --> 01:02:43,870
- Your therapy? - No. Medcom's.

626
01:02:43,940 --> 01:02:46,360
Do I call you Miss Medcom?

627
01:02:46,440 --> 01:02:49,820
If you like, Dr. Hall. My name's Karen Anson.

628
01:02:49,890 --> 01:02:54,680
Good. I couldn't cope with two machines. How does this work?

629
01:02:54,760 --> 01:02:58,470
You're lucky. Medcom's got one of the best minds here.

630
01:02:58,530 --> 01:03:02,310
It's a medical data analyzer that can diagnose as well as prescribe.

631
01:03:02,370 --> 01:03:05,370
It's hooked up to the main computer on level 1.

632
01:03:06,020 --> 01:03:08,090
Every console and instrument in Wildfire...

633
01:03:08,170 --> 01:03:11,360
